Well, yeah, for sure.

1294
01:03:01,739 --> 01:03:03,340
That's really nice of you.

1295
01:03:04,139 --> 01:03:06,699
Well, you know, I need a new roof.

1296
01:03:10,219 --> 01:03:11,179
It's time.

1297
01:03:11,179 --> 01:03:11,980
Practical, too.

1298
01:03:13,259 --> 01:03:15,179
Is anybody else looking to purchase anything?

1299
01:03:16,300 --> 01:03:16,800
No.

1300
01:03:17,820 --> 01:03:20,619
I'd like to buy the oil of etherealness.

1301
01:03:21,420 --> 01:03:29,659
Oh, yes. Now, this is a special, special elixir.

1302
01:03:30,539 --> 01:03:38,219
And I hold of this little vial, really, of oil.

1303
01:03:39,500 --> 01:03:45,259
This can take you to the borders of the ethereal plane.

1304
01:03:49,739 --> 01:03:52,859
That sounds like just the kind of place I would want to go.

1305
01:03:55,659 --> 01:03:57,980
This is just a single use, right?

1306
01:03:57,980 --> 01:03:58,779
A single use.

1307
01:03:59,580 --> 01:04:01,260
Yes, this is single use.

1308
01:04:02,620 --> 01:04:04,860
It's good for a fair amount of time.

1309
01:04:04,860 --> 01:04:09,500
You know, like, a long sleep worth of time.

1310
01:04:11,500 --> 01:04:14,780
Yeah, but it is single use, yes.

1311
01:04:17,420 --> 01:04:19,820
OK, well, I think I have enough money to buy it.

1312
01:04:19,820 --> 01:04:23,340
If maybe you wouldn't mind cutting me a little bit of a deal.

1313
01:04:24,540 --> 01:04:25,019
What do you think?

1314
01:04:25,019 --> 01:04:30,860
Well, Moop might need some help putting that those those shingles up.

1315
01:04:32,539 --> 01:04:36,300
And, you know, a big strong person like you working in the store.

1316
01:04:36,300 --> 01:04:37,820
I didn't know I'd be doing the roof.

1317
01:04:40,380 --> 01:04:42,219
She said she needed a new roof.

1318
01:04:42,219 --> 01:04:43,099
That's true. She did.

1319
01:04:43,099 --> 01:04:44,860
I just didn't know why I didn't make that connection.

1320
01:04:47,500 --> 01:04:50,780
Wait, do you think a brick, a brickery would help out with that as well?

1321
01:04:50,780 --> 01:04:52,300
Is that like a transferable skill?

1322
01:04:52,620 --> 01:04:59,180
No, I think a shingler and a brickery are just two very different vocations.

1323
01:04:59,740 --> 01:05:01,980
Yeah, I don't think my roof needs bricks.

1324
01:05:03,660 --> 01:05:04,860
Yeah, probably too heavy.

1325
01:05:04,860 --> 01:05:05,660
Well, is it OK?

1326
01:05:05,660 --> 01:05:06,780
I know he's going to come at eight.

1327
01:05:06,780 --> 01:05:07,660
I do my Zumba class.

1328
01:05:07,660 --> 01:05:08,860
Can I come over after that?

1329
01:05:08,860 --> 01:05:10,539
Yeah, you know, it could.

1330
01:05:10,539 --> 01:05:14,300
Could I take the Zumba class for Zumba?

1331
01:05:14,300 --> 01:05:15,580
Class is open to anybody.

1332
01:05:15,580 --> 01:05:16,460
You come whenever you want.

1333
01:05:16,460 --> 01:05:17,340
Fantastic.

1334
01:05:17,340 --> 01:05:19,100
I will show up for Zumba then.

1335
01:05:19,659 --> 01:05:25,420
Sally notices just how nice and accommodating Bombardy is being.

1336
01:05:25,420 --> 01:05:32,779
And out from his cloak, he produces a, what is it?

1337
01:05:32,779 --> 01:05:36,219
It is the scroll of vitriolic sphere.

1338
01:05:36,219 --> 01:05:39,179
And it's like and puts it out on the table

1339
01:05:40,139 --> 01:05:43,659
and then puts down 480 gold pieces.

1340
01:05:46,539 --> 01:05:48,539
And is like, I would like to purchase this, please.

1341
01:05:49,339 --> 01:05:49,839
Hmm.

1342
01:05:50,539 --> 01:05:51,039
Hmm.

1343
01:05:51,579 --> 01:05:57,099
Well, we're close enough.

1344
01:05:57,099 --> 01:05:57,599
Thank you.

1345
01:06:02,460 --> 01:06:04,219
Just some straight commerce for Sally.

1346
01:06:04,219 --> 01:06:09,420
Seems out of character, but as we mentioned, who knows what else he stole.

1347
01:06:09,420 --> 01:06:11,420
Yeah, pay for something.

1348
01:06:11,420 --> 01:06:13,819
Pretty sure that none of you have any money anymore.

1349
01:06:13,819 --> 01:06:15,259
No, I'm pretty sure it's all gone.

1350
01:06:16,460 --> 01:06:18,699
Some of you have part-time jobs now.

1351
01:06:18,940 --> 01:06:24,620
And just a short period part-time job while we throw that roof up there.

1352
01:06:24,620 --> 01:06:24,940
That's right.

1353
01:06:24,940 --> 01:06:28,060
Me and Moot are both strapping, so it should be.

1354
01:06:28,620 --> 01:06:32,300
I got that little crab claw that will help me out for the hard-to-reach places.

1355
01:06:32,300 --> 01:06:32,860
For sure.

1356
01:06:32,860 --> 01:06:34,780
When we need to bring more shingles up to the roof,

1357
01:06:34,780 --> 01:06:36,380
we don't have to go back up and down.

1358
01:06:36,380 --> 01:06:40,060
You can just mage hand those up to the top of the roof.

1359
01:06:40,620 --> 01:06:46,540
Well, we fade out on Moot and Glim doing some of that work,

1360
01:06:46,539 --> 01:06:48,860
hammering those shingles in real well,

1361
01:06:49,579 --> 01:06:54,860
as the sun is now setting over the dock ward in Waterdeep.

